{
  "texts": [
    "The technology could be adapted for smartphones, enhancing computational photography with richer, more detailed information.",
    "This technology may also allow agricultural robots to utilize hyperspectral imaging rather than just RGB vision, expanding their functional capabilities.",
    "The primary advantage of this technology lies in its ability to facilitate quick, non-destructive quality checks of agricultural products without additional costs or complexities.",
    "The effectiveness of hyperspectral reconstruction largely depends on its capacity to capture spectral signatures from the near-infrared (NIR) region (700-2500 nm).",
    "This spectral range is crucial as it provides detailed structural information related to molecular vibrations, which are key in determining the quality attributes of agricultural products (Kamruzzaman et al. 2022)."
  ]
}